In Python you can store various types of data in variables, including numbers, strings, lists, and dictionaries.
In Python you can define functions to encapsulate reusable blocks of code and organize your programs.
In Python you can control program flow using conditional statements (if/elif/else) and loops (for/while).
In Python you can work with files, reading from them and writing to them to persist data.
In Python you can utilize a vast ecosystem of libraries and modules to extend functionality for tasks like web development, data analysis, and more.